  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that offer system-wide dictionary and word lookup functionality:\n\n1. Google Translate\n- Can translate and define words across the system\n- Supports multiple languages\n- Easy to use with quick lookup\n\n2. Dictionary.com\n- Offers system-wide word definitions\n- Supports word lookup in multiple contexts\n- Provides synonyms and etymology\n\n3. Universal Dictionary\n- Allows lookup across different apps\n- Works with text selection\n- Supports multiple languages\n\n4. Popup Dictionary\n- Provides pop-up definitions when text is selected\n- Works system-wide\n- Simple and lightweight\n\n5. Everywhere Dictionary\n- Allows dictionary lookup in any app\n- Quick and easy to use\n- Supports multiple dictionaries\n\nMost of these apps have a floating button or use the Android share/lookup menu to provide definitions across different applications. Some may require specific permissions or settings to work system-wide.\n\nI recommend trying a few to see which one best fits your specific needs and device compatibility.",
